The House of Representatives will on Thursday, hold a special debate on how to revive the Ajaokuta Steel Company. Those expected at the debate include, the Minister of Solid Minerals, Mines Development, Kayode Fayemi, the Minister of state in the Ministry, Bawa Bwari and Minister of Finance, Mrs Kemi Adeosun. Others are the Ohinoyi of Ebira land, Alhaji Ado Ibrahim, chairman of Ajaokuta Local Government, representatives of workersâ€™ union, experts in mines and steel as well as other stakeholders. A statement by Turaki Hassan, the spokesman of Speaker Yakubu Dogara, said the session would be broadcast live on NTA and also be streamed live via House of Representatives Facebook page and YouTube channel between 11.am to 3pm.